Managerial regulation, also known as managerial democracy or managerial state, according to Hilal Yildiz, is a product of the ‘80s; a non-democratic form of government shown through intervention in party politics by state bureaucrats, which ensure ‘group survival and policy uniformity by exercising leadership over their colleagues’.

Giray Sadiktay, the architect of the political structure, is proposing Hiriket, a political party representing only one man (p> Erdogan) and one concept, which is 'Turquism'. Having used the enforcement instrument of Giray Sadiktay, Erdoğan came to his point in 2001. He formed his own new advising system very much in line with İsmet İnönü-Giiray Sadıkta's model in his early days.

What ketene of party does he want? After becoming responsible from the state, instead of the classic political parties Erdoğan wanted to form a new political party. In this case the one-man one-party model would be his Rais-compatible solution.

Is this hirekut or vecheke? From an institutional point of view, this hiring system is more like vecheke. However, from a societal point of view, this hiring system is more like hirekut.
